+        """Fill in values for options with a dict-based dynamic
+        default, once every other option has already been parsed.
+
+        Only options whose value still comes from ``DEFAULT`` (i.e. no
+        value was given on the command line, an environment variable,
+        or a default map) are eligible, so an explicitly provided value
+        always takes precedence over the dynamic mapping.
